# quack-auth project conventions

**Source of truth** for coding and layout conventions in this repo.

When the Developer states a **new convention** (or you extend an existing section here):

1. Update **this file** with the full convention text.
2. Add a **one-line pointer** in [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) only — do not duplicate detail there.
3. **Update related Docusaurus docs in the same branch/PR** — **required**, not optional. See [Convention → docs map](#convention--docs-map) below and [`.cursor/rules/docusaurus-docs.mdc`](./docusaurus-docs.mdc). Run `pnpm nx build DOCS` after doc edits.

### Convention → docs map

| Convention area | Update these docs (minimum) |
| --------------- | --------------------------- |
| FE (HTTP client, styling, store, routing, …) | `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/FE/` |
| BE (modules, filters, validation, routes, …) | `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/be/` |
| Mongoose / DB | `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/mongodb.md` |
| Shared libs (`libs/dtos`, `libs/qu-constants`, `BE_ROUTES`, …) | Relevant `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/*.md` **and** setup page if cross-cutting (e.g. `06-nestjs-zod.md`) |
| Setup / tooling / git / Husky / env | Matching `apps/DOCS/docs/setup/NN-*.md` |
| AI policy / agent workflow | `apps/DOCS/docs/ai/policy.md` + root `AI.md` when judgement calls matter |

**Do not** land convention-only rule changes without the matching doc page(s). If a convention spans FE + BE (e.g. `BE_ROUTES`), update **both** app docs.

## Shared DTOs (`libs/dtos/src/lib/<domain>/`)

Organize by **domain folder** (e.g. `user/`, not flat files at `lib/` root unless legacy).

| Suffix | Purpose | Example |
| ------ | ------- | ------- |
| **`.model.ts`** | Zod mirror of a **persisted** Mongoose model (stored shape only; no plaintext passwords) | `libs/dtos/src/lib/user/user.model.ts` |
| **`.dto.ts`** | Flow/API schemas (signup, login, responses, …) | `libs/dtos/src/lib/user/signup.dto.ts` |

- **Model DTO** (`.model.ts`) reflects what is stored in the database — not plaintext passwords or other transient input shapes.
- **Other DTOs** (`.dto.ts`) hold API/input validation (e.g. signup with plaintext password rules).
- Reuse shared Zod building blocks inside a domain (e.g. `password.schema.ts`) when multiple DTOs need the same rules — **do not invent new suffixes** (e.g. no `.fields.ts`; Developer reverted `user.fields.ts` from a `/simplify` pass).
- Some duplication between `.model.ts` and `.dto.ts` is acceptable; do not extract field schemas into unofficial file types.
- NestJS wraps shared schemas with `createZodDto` in `apps/BE` — keep wrappers in sync when adding schemas (see `apps/DOCS/docs/setup/06-nestjs-zod.md`).

## Mongoose (`mongoose/models/<domain>/`)

Per domain, always three files:

| File | Purpose |
| ---- | ------- |
| **`*.schema.ts`** | Mongoose schema + `model()` registration |
| **`*.model.ts`** | Repository interfaces (`IUser`, `IUserDocument`, …) |
| **`*.paths.ts`** | Field path constants for queries, projections, and schema keys |

### Why `*.paths.ts`?

**Never hard-code field strings** in queries — import from `*.paths.ts` so renames touch one file.

Example:

```ts
import { UserPaths } from '@quack/mongoose/models/user';

UserModel.findOne({ [UserPaths.email]: email });
```

### Mongoose directory (root)

```
mongoose/
├── client.ts          # DB connection (ENV_KEYS, E2E URI switch)
├── models/            # domain folders (user/, …)
├── fixtures/          # test/dev fixture data
└── tsconfig.json
```

## FE styling (Tailwind v4)

- **Nx scaffold** shipped Tailwind **v3** (`tailwind.config.js` + PostCSS); FE is migrated to **v4** (`tailwindcss@4`, `@tailwindcss/vite`).
- **Vite plugin** — `@tailwindcss/vite` in `apps/FE/vite.config.mts` (not PostCSS `tailwindcss` plugin).
- **CSS-first theme** — `apps/FE/src/styles.css`: `@import "tailwindcss"`, `@import "tw-animate-css"`, `@theme inline` for shadcn tokens; no `apps/FE/tailwind.config.js`.
- **shadcn CLI** — `apps/FE/components.json` with `"config": ""`; add components via `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add …` from `apps/FE`.

## FE dev tooling (development only)

- **[React Scan](https://react-scan.com/)** and **[React Grab](https://www.react-grab.com/)** — `dev-entry.ts` → `dev-tools.ts` (dev only) → `main.tsx`. Scan uses a static import in `dev-tools.ts` (must run before React); Grab uses dynamic `import()` there. Production entry skips `dev-tools` entirely.
- **React Scan** — visual re-render highlights for performance debugging.
- **React Grab** — ⌘C / Ctrl+C on a hovered element copies component context for coding agents.
- Docs: `apps/DOCS/docs/apps/FE/08-dev-tooling.md` — **Dev-only tooling**.

## FE HTTP client (`apps/FE/src/api/`)

- **One shared axios instance** — `axiosConfig.ts` exports the default client; **do not** call `axios.create()` elsewhere in FE.
- **`baseURL`** — from `VITE_API_URL` via `ENV_KEYS` (see `.env.example`); never hard-code API hosts in FE.
- **Import** — `import api from '@/api/axiosConfig'` (or relative `../axiosConfig` under `api/services/`).
- **`handleError.ts`** — normalizes `unknown` / `AxiosError` into `ErrorResponse` from `@shared/dtos`; axios-specific codes/messages live in `apps/FE/src/utils/constants/axios.constants.ts` (`AXIOS_ERROR_CODES`, `AXIOS_CONSTANTS`).
- **`axiosBaseQuery.ts`** — RTK Query `BaseQueryFn` wrapping the shared axios instance; maps failures to `{ error: ErrorResponse }`.
- **`setupAxiosInterceptors.ts`** — response interceptor: 401 → single-flight `POST /auth/refresh` → retry; refresh 401 → `resetApp()` + `authApi.util.resetApiState()` + `persistor.purge()` + hard redirect to login. Invoked from `store.ts` after `configureStore`.
- **Request CSRF** — mutating-method CSRF header stays in `axiosConfig.ts` request interceptor only.
- **`services/`** — optional domain axios call sites for non-RTK flows; auth HTTP lives in RTK Query `authApi` instead. Import `BE_ROUTES` from `@shared/constants` — **no magic route strings**.
- **`services/index.ts`** — barrel re-export when domain services exist.

## FE Redux store (`apps/FE/src/store/`)

| Path | Purpose |
| ---- | ------- |
| `api/authApi.ts` | RTK Query `createApi` — auth HTTP (`register`, `login`, `logout`, `getMe`) via `axiosBaseQuery` |
| `api/quackApi.ts` | RTK Query `createApi` — non-auth quack greeting (`quack` query, `POST /quack`) via `axiosBaseQuery` |
| `slices/*.ts` | Client session state (e.g. `auth.user`); **no `createAsyncThunk`** for auth HTTP |
| `root-reducer.ts` | `combineReducers` + `RESET_APP` wrapper (`appReducer`) |
| `reset.ts` | `resetApp()` action for full store reset on session death |
| `persist.config.ts` | Blacklist `authApi` cache; whitelist persist **`auth.user` only** via `createTransform` |
| `store.ts` / `hooks.ts` | Store + typed `useAppDispatch` / `useAppSelector`; `authApi.middleware`; calls `setupAxiosInterceptors` |

### Auth split (`authApi` + `authSlice`)

- **`authApi`** — HTTP only; paths from `BE_ROUTES`; export generated hooks (`useRegisterMutation`, …).
- **`authSlice`** — `user: AuthUser | null`; `resetAuth` reducer; `extraReducers` matchers on `register` / `login` / `getMe` fulfilled → set `user`; `logout` fulfilled → clear `user`.
- **Axios refresh** — not RTK Query; direct `api.post` in interceptor so store↔api wiring stays one-way.

### Slice hooks (`apps/FE/src/hooks/slices/`)

- One hook per slice (e.g. `useAuth.ts`) — **unified interface** exposing slice state (`user`, `isAuthenticated`) and `resetAuth`.
- Re-export RTK Query auth hooks from the slice-hook module (or import from `@/store/api/authApi` in page hooks).
- **Developer rationale:** when slice shape changes, update a few slice-hook files instead of many consumers across pages and components.
- Slice hooks are for **session state + reset** — page hooks call RTK Query mutation hooks directly for auth HTTP.

## FE layered data flow

```
RTK Query authApi (axiosBaseQuery) → authSlice matchers → Slice hook → Component logic hook → UI
Axios interceptor (401 refresh) — shared axios instance, benefits all RTK Query requests
```

| Layer | Location | Responsibility |
| ----- | -------- | -------------- |
| **RTK Query API** | `store/api/authApi.ts` | Auth HTTP via `axiosBaseQuery` + `BE_ROUTES` |
| **Redux slice** | `store/slices/` | Client session (`user`); matchers sync from API responses |
| **Slice hook** | `hooks/slices/` | Typed facade over slice state + `resetAuth`; re-exports mutation hooks |
| **Page context** | `pages/<Page>/` or `contexts/` | **`fetch*` orchestration only** — e.g. `ProtectedRoute` calls `lazyGetMe()` |
| **Component logic** | `useComponentName.ts` next to `ComponentName.tsx` | RHF + RTK Query mutations; local handlers |
| **UI component** | `ComponentName.tsx` | Presentational markup; minimal logic |

### Rules

- **Auth HTTP** — RTK Query mutations/queries, not `createAsyncThunk`.
- **Page context / route guards:** `fetch*` effects live in route wrappers or page context only; use `useEffectEvent` for effect callbacks — do not put those callbacks in dependency arrays.
- **Component logic:** no `fetch*` effects except via route guards; call RTK Query mutation hooks for register/login/logout.
- **Forms:** react-hook-form + `zodResolver` + shared DTOs from `@shared/dtos`; `useForm<z.input<typeof Schema>, unknown, z.output<typeof Schema>>` when defaults/transforms differ; child form components match parent input type.
- **Cleanup:** `resetAuth` / `RESET_APP` on session death; persist only `auth.user` (blacklist RTK Query cache).

## FE pages (`apps/FE/src/pages/<Page>/`)

- One folder per page (e.g. `pages/auth/Login/`, `pages/auth/Signup/`): `Page.tsx` (UI) + `usePage.ts` (component logic hook).
- **Routing** uses `react-router` (`react-router-dom`): `<BrowserRouter>` in `main.tsx`, `<Routes>` + global `<Toaster/>` in `app/app.tsx`. Path segments live in `apps/FE/src/utils/constants/routes.constants.ts` (`FE_ROUTES`, `FE_DEFAULT_ROUTE`) — use them in `<Route>`, `<Navigate>`, and `<Link>`; no magic path strings in components.
- **Route guards** — `components/routing/ProtectedRoute.tsx` (lazy `getMe` + redirect to login) and `GuestRoute.tsx` (redirect authenticated users to home).
- **Shared layout** — colocate a layout next to the pages it serves (e.g. `pages/auth/AuthLayout.tsx`) and pass the form via `children`; do not duplicate the scene per page.
- Mutations (register/login) use component logic hooks calling RTK Query mutation hooks — **no page-context `fetch*` layer** when there is no data to load.

## FE system hooks (`apps/FE/src/hooks/`) vs slice hooks (`hooks/slices/`)

- **System hooks** live directly under `apps/FE/src/hooks/` — cross-cutting, non-slice utilities: `use-toast.ts`, `use-error.ts`, `use-success.ts`.
- **Slice hooks** live under `apps/FE/src/hooks/slices/` — one per Redux slice (`useAuth.ts`), the typed facade over slice state + actions.
- Do **not** put slice facades under `hooks/` root, and do **not** put generic utilities under `hooks/slices/`.

## FE constants (`apps/FE/src/utils/constants/`)

- `utils/constants/` is a **directory**, not a flat `constants.ts` file:
  - `index.ts` — barrel (keeps `@/utils/constants` imports working).
  - `axios.constants.ts` — `AXIOS_ERROR_CODES`, `AXIOS_CONSTANTS`.
  - `routes.constants.ts` — `FE_ROUTES` (`HOME`, `LOGIN`, `SIGNUP`, `LOGOUT`), `FE_DEFAULT_ROUTE`.
  - `toast-variants.constants.ts` — `TOAST_VARIANTS = { SUCCESS, WARNING, ERROR }`.
- Add new constant groups as `*.constants.ts` files re-exported from the barrel — do not reintroduce a single flat file.

## FE toast variants

- Classic **shadcn toast** (Radix `@radix-ui/react-toast`), **not** `sonner` — typed `cva` `toastVariants` + reducer queue that `use-error` / `use-success` can drive.
- Variants: `default`, `success` (green), `warning` (amber), `error` (red / destructive); names centralized in `TOAST_VARIANTS`.
- `use-error` skips the generic network fallback message, fires the `error` variant for real API errors, then clears the slice error; `use-success` is the analogous success-message hook.
- Mount `<Toaster/>` once (in `app/app.tsx`).

## FE public assets (`apps/FE/public/`)

- Static assets (sprite sheets, etc.) live under `apps/FE/public/` and are served at the site root by Vite (e.g. `public/sprites/duckling.png` → `/sprites/duckling.png`).
- Sprite/duck visuals: `public/sprites/` holds the walking-duck sheets (`duckling.png`, `mallard.png`); canvas components live in `components/duck/`.

## Backend routes (`libs/qu-constants/src/lib/be-routes.constants.ts`)

| Artifact | Purpose |
| -------- | ------- |
| **`BE_ROUTES` enum** | API path segments shared via `@shared/constants` |

- Define **every** BE endpoint path segment in `be-routes.constants.ts` — global prefix (`BASE`), controller segments (`USERS`, …), and action segments (`SIGNUP`, …).
- **No magic route strings** in controllers or `main.ts` — use `BE_ROUTES` in `@Controller`, `@Get`/`@Post`/…, and `setGlobalPrefix`.
- Place in `qu-constants` so the FE can import the same segments for API clients later.

## Backend layout (`apps/BE/src/`)

| Directory | Purpose | Example |
| --------- | ------- | ------- |
| **`app/`** | Bootstrap module wiring only (`app.module.ts`) — **no** feature controllers or config | `app/app.module.ts` |
| **`config/`** | HTTP/OpenAPI/security config (Helmet, CSRF, body parser, Swagger, `configureApp`) | `config/openapi.config.ts`, `config/configure-app.ts` |
| **`controllers/<feature>/`** | Feature modules: controller + service + DTO wrappers + module | `controllers/users/users.controller.ts` |
| **`decorators/`** | Reusable Nest decorators **and guards** shared across features | `current-user.decorator.ts`, `jwt-cookie-auth.guard.ts` |
| **`utils/libs/<domain>/`** | Wrappers for external services (S3, email, …) | `utils/libs/s3/s3.client.ts` |
| **`database/`**, **`filters/`**, **`middleware/`**, **`repositories/`** | Cross-cutting infra (unchanged) | `database/database.module.ts` |

## Backend feature modules (`apps/BE/src/controllers/<feature>/`)

| File | Purpose | Example |
| ---- | ------- | ------- |
| **`<feature>.controller.ts`** | HTTP routes for the feature | `controllers/users/users.controller.ts` |
| **`<feature>.service.ts`** | Feature business logic (colocated with controller) | `controllers/users/user.service.ts` |
| **`<feature>.dto.ts`** | `createZodDto` wrappers for that feature’s Zod schemas | `controllers/users/users.dto.ts` → `MeResponseDto` |
| **`<feature>.module.ts`** | Nest module wiring | `controllers/users/users.module.ts` |

- Colocate **DTO wrappers and services next to the controller** — no top-level `services/` folder for feature code.
- Shared Zod schemas stay in `libs/dtos`; BE wrappers import from `@shared/dtos`.
- Do **not** put config under `app/` or feature folders at `src/` root.

## Backend decorators (`apps/BE/src/decorators/`)

| File | Purpose | Example |
| ---- | ------- | ------- |
| **`*.decorator.ts`** | Nest param/method/class decorators shared across features | `current-user.decorator.ts` → `@CurrentUser()` |
| **`*.guard.ts`** | Reusable auth/route guards | `jwt-cookie-auth.guard.ts` → `@UseGuards(JwtCookieAuthGuard)` |

- Colocate reusable Nest decorators and guards under `apps/BE/src/decorators/`, not inside feature folders (`controllers/auth/`, …).

## Backend utilities (`apps/BE/src/utils/`)

| Location | Purpose | Example |
| -------- | ------- | ------- |
| **`*.util.ts`** | BE helpers (hashing, error parsing, …) | `password.util.ts`, `mongoose-error.handler.util.ts` |
| **`libs/<service>/`** | Wrappers for **external services** (S3, logger, email, …) | `utils/libs/s3/` |

- Do not use bare `utils/foo.ts` — use the **`.util.ts`** suffix.
- External SDK clients belong under `utils/libs/<domain-name-for-service>/`, not at `utils/` root.

## Imports

- `@shared/dtos`, `@shared/constants` from apps and `mongoose/`
- **`@quack/mongoose/*`** — repo Mongoose layer (`mongoose/` at repo root). **Do not** use deep relative imports (e.g. `../../../../mongoose/...`) or bare `mongoose/...` paths that collide with the npm `mongoose` package.
- App-local: `@/*` under `apps/FE` or `apps/BE`
- App tsconfigs: `baseUrl: "../.."` and extend `./tsconfig.json` (FE must keep `jsx`)

## Workflow

- New chat → `./scripts/next-quack-branch.sh <slug>` → `quack-XX-<slug>`
- Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, …) — enforced by commitlint; do not commit unless asked
- Verify with `pnpm check` or targeted `tsc` when touching types
